cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a distributed wireless content caching system. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the trade-off between storage capacity and repair bandwidth. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of broadcast messages to repair failed cache nodes. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with a distributed system and the repair of partially failed nodes. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may discuss security implications of the caching system.
